1
00:00:00,300 --> 00:00:01,433
welcome back

2
00:00:01,600 --> 00:00:04,666
today we are going to make some rocket fuel

3
00:00:04,800 --> 00:00:07,700
and the first step is to make phthalic acid

4
00:00:08,033 --> 00:00:10,433
which is made with potassium dichromate

5
00:00:11,033 --> 00:00:13,000
this can be made in many ways

6
00:00:13,000 --> 00:00:16,800
but the fastest one requires a ZPM chemical reactor

7
00:00:17,133 --> 00:00:20,133
since we don't even have access to LuV

8
00:00:20,200 --> 00:00:23,633
we shall do that by using 8 IV energy hatches

9
00:00:24,200 --> 00:00:27,600
once we have fully charged the batteries for that setup

10
00:00:27,600 --> 00:00:30,000
we can see that this thing doesn't work

11
00:00:30,300 --> 00:00:30,733
and thus

12
00:00:30,733 --> 00:00:33,166
we shall have two additional small reactors

13
00:00:33,166 --> 00:00:35,700
to soften the process requirements

14
00:00:35,933 --> 00:00:38,400
and now we can get the potassium dichromate

15
00:00:38,400 --> 00:00:40,100
for the ferric acid

16
00:00:40,633 --> 00:00:42,833
fermentic acid has many usages

17
00:00:42,833 --> 00:00:44,866
and the first one we will want to do

18
00:00:44,866 --> 00:00:47,000
is to make diphosphoric acid

19
00:00:47,933 --> 00:00:49,933
which is one of the two ingredients

20
00:00:49,933 --> 00:00:52,400
needed for making polybenzimidazole

21
00:00:52,466 --> 00:00:54,600
also known as PBI

22
00:00:55,666 --> 00:00:58,800
the other ingredient is 3,3-diaminobenzidine

23
00:01:00,533 --> 00:01:05,333
which can easily be synthesized from 3,3-dichlorobenzidine

24
00:01:06,033 --> 00:01:08,900
which we make out of 2-Nitro chlorobenzene

25
00:01:09,600 --> 00:01:11,266
now that we have PBI

26
00:01:11,266 --> 00:01:13,800
we can assemble a better Thermal Protection

27
00:01:13,800 --> 00:01:17,300
which will help us survive the harsh outer space exploration

28
00:01:17,300 --> 00:01:19,333
that we will do with our new rocket

29
00:01:19,733 --> 00:01:22,300
but it looks like we have forgotten something

30
00:01:22,700 --> 00:01:26,200
the reason why we made ferric acid was not for PBI

31
00:01:26,333 --> 00:01:27,833
but for rocket fuel

32
00:01:27,933 --> 00:01:30,633
so we go back to dehydrating some of it

33
00:01:30,633 --> 00:01:33,066
to get some phthalic anhydride

34
00:01:33,500 --> 00:01:35,600
we bring that to our chemical plant

35
00:01:35,600 --> 00:01:37,600
where we react it with ethylbenzene

36
00:01:37,600 --> 00:01:40,233
to get some 2-ethylanthraquinone

37
00:01:40,666 --> 00:01:42,333
since that is a catalyst

38
00:01:42,333 --> 00:01:44,733
we get that fluid to an automated setup

39
00:01:44,733 --> 00:01:46,266
for further processing

40
00:01:46,700 --> 00:01:50,900
this chemical plant is going to self feed on itself a lot of its products

41
00:01:50,900 --> 00:01:53,133
but let's see them one at a time

42
00:01:53,933 --> 00:01:54,400
first

43
00:01:54,400 --> 00:01:59,100
we turn the 2-ethylanthraquinone into 2-ethylanthrahydroquinone

44
00:01:59,500 --> 00:02:02,533
which we use to make hydrogen peroxide

45
00:02:02,700 --> 00:02:06,333
that will also give back some 2-ethylanthraquinone

46
00:02:06,666 --> 00:02:10,200
finally we add some other stuff to make hydrazine

47
00:02:11,033 --> 00:02:13,466
and here we have all the inputs

48
00:02:13,500 --> 00:02:17,100
now all we have to do is to push the start button

49
00:02:18,666 --> 00:02:21,333
and once the hydrazine is produced

50
00:02:21,333 --> 00:02:24,000
we can retrieve it from our main terminal

51
00:02:25,100 --> 00:02:28,933
we manually add some methanol to obtain dense hydrazine

52
00:02:28,933 --> 00:02:32,666
which is a fuel rocket that can work with our tier 3 rocket

53
00:02:34,200 --> 00:02:36,433
and once we loaded our new rocket

54
00:02:36,433 --> 00:02:39,500
we can take off to the new planets and moons

55
00:02:40,466 --> 00:02:43,133
and the main destination is going to be Ceres

56
00:02:43,133 --> 00:02:46,000
where we can find platinum veins

57
00:02:46,333 --> 00:02:48,333
while we wait for our miners

58
00:02:48,333 --> 00:02:52,233
we can do the last chemical chain of the IV Quest page

59
00:02:52,233 --> 00:02:53,266
monazite

60
00:02:53,900 --> 00:02:56,600
this chemical line requires some crush ores

61
00:02:56,600 --> 00:02:59,533
which we are already processing in other ways

62
00:02:59,800 --> 00:03:01,866
to ensure it gets to that line

63
00:03:01,900 --> 00:03:05,266
we use a high priority storage bus on a drawer

64
00:03:06,200 --> 00:03:06,933
and here

65
00:03:06,933 --> 00:03:10,500
instead of the usual mineral processing machines

66
00:03:10,500 --> 00:03:14,233
we use a digester to digest those heavy rocks

67
00:03:15,033 --> 00:03:17,933
the output then goes into a dissolution tank

68
00:03:18,200 --> 00:03:23,200
and this machine requires the inputs to have a specific ratio to be able to work

69
00:03:23,800 --> 00:03:27,333
so we are going to move the fluids slowly and steady steps

70
00:03:27,333 --> 00:03:30,933
with covers that will control the level inside the hatches

71
00:03:31,466 --> 00:03:33,600
and this seems to work as intended

72
00:03:33,600 --> 00:03:37,666
by stopping once we reach 9 metric cubes of fluid

73
00:03:37,933 --> 00:03:40,333
we do the same with the other input

74
00:03:40,933 --> 00:03:44,300
and once we have properly regulated the fluid inputs

75
00:03:44,300 --> 00:03:48,300
we can start the second processing step in the dissolution tank

76
00:03:48,866 --> 00:03:52,233
the output has to be sifted to get a lot of products

77
00:03:52,233 --> 00:03:56,100
but the one we care the most is the monazite sulfate dust

78
00:03:56,833 --> 00:03:59,000
which we bath in some acid

79
00:03:59,500 --> 00:04:00,866
then we sift it again

80
00:04:01,433 --> 00:04:04,100
we give it a quick dry in a blast furnace

81
00:04:04,666 --> 00:04:06,700
we react with nitric acid

82
00:04:07,400 --> 00:04:09,500
we mix in some other chemicals

83
00:04:10,266 --> 00:04:13,866
then we run that poor compound in a sifter one more time

84
00:04:14,266 --> 00:04:16,900
and we vacuum freeze the outputs

85
00:04:17,633 --> 00:04:22,266
using the new upcoming polarizer in electromagnetic separator mode

86
00:04:22,300 --> 00:04:25,600
we take out stuff that may not even be ferromagnetic

87
00:04:25,733 --> 00:04:28,300
we reuse the previous EBF to extract

88
00:04:28,300 --> 00:04:32,533
heterogeneous halogenic monazite rare earth mixture dust

89
00:04:32,666 --> 00:04:36,266
we mix it with other stuff up to its saturation point

90
00:04:36,466 --> 00:04:39,533
and then I guess we separate what we just mixed in

91
00:04:39,800 --> 00:04:43,000
from which we can finally sift out some samarium

92
00:04:43,133 --> 00:04:46,466
this is going to be required for the motors of the next tier

93
00:04:46,633 --> 00:04:49,033
we followed the main processing path

94
00:04:49,033 --> 00:04:52,333
but there are some byproduct we have left behind

95
00:04:52,333 --> 00:04:54,233
so we shall gather those too

96
00:04:54,600 --> 00:04:58,000
but we mostly reused the same machines

97
00:04:58,433 --> 00:05:01,266
and we shall also do the bastnasite line

98
00:05:01,266 --> 00:05:04,100
since we are doing weird mineral lines

99
00:05:04,233 --> 00:05:05,733
this is more streamlined

100
00:05:05,733 --> 00:05:07,933
and the main output is holmium

101
00:05:08,100 --> 00:05:09,333
we are once again

102
00:05:09,333 --> 00:05:12,466
going to reuse as many machines as possible

103
00:05:12,866 --> 00:05:16,300
now we can go back to Ceres to retrieve our platinum

104
00:05:16,300 --> 00:05:17,633
and once back

105
00:05:17,633 --> 00:05:20,033
we find a nice surprise

106
00:05:20,233 --> 00:05:22,033
we also have gathered some naquadah

107
00:05:22,033 --> 00:05:26,066
which will allow us to start one more funny chemical line

108
00:05:26,833 --> 00:05:30,066
unlike the previous artificial chemical processing

109
00:05:30,066 --> 00:05:34,433
this line is going to be more based on fantasy and imagination

110
00:05:34,833 --> 00:05:38,000
we start by preparing some shaved ice

111
00:05:38,700 --> 00:05:40,900
then we add some Antimony aroma

112
00:05:40,933 --> 00:05:42,600
but they added too much flavor

113
00:05:42,600 --> 00:05:45,700
and now it look like one of the previous chemicals

114
00:05:46,300 --> 00:05:47,666
so we try to distill it

115
00:05:47,666 --> 00:05:51,100
to see how much more we can concentrate the aroma

116
00:05:51,733 --> 00:05:54,100
but we want it to be slightly sour

117
00:05:54,100 --> 00:05:56,100
so we make it more acid

118
00:05:56,800 --> 00:05:57,433
and now

119
00:05:57,433 --> 00:06:00,733
it is the perfect moment to add in the main ingredient

120
00:06:00,733 --> 00:06:01,800
the naquadah

121
00:06:02,666 --> 00:06:03,700
after heating it

122
00:06:03,700 --> 00:06:07,533
we centrifuge out some of the residue of the artificial aroma

123
00:06:08,600 --> 00:06:11,000
now this is still low quality

124
00:06:11,000 --> 00:06:15,433
so we have to add some seasoning such as P-507

125
00:06:16,200 --> 00:06:18,033
and as you can see

126
00:06:18,033 --> 00:06:20,666
our naquadah is no longer low quality

127
00:06:20,666 --> 00:06:24,000
since we have used some good P-507

128
00:06:24,100 --> 00:06:26,833
made by manually farming some organic nuts

129
00:06:26,833 --> 00:06:28,600
for its oil component

130
00:06:29,266 --> 00:06:32,833
the last touch is to activate the neutrons inside our dish

131
00:06:32,833 --> 00:06:34,900
to make it feel funny on the tongue

132
00:06:35,866 --> 00:06:36,400
however

133
00:06:36,400 --> 00:06:40,200
we do not have the cooking tools required for such tasks

134
00:06:40,200 --> 00:06:40,966
to make one

135
00:06:40,966 --> 00:06:43,033
we need a precision assembler

136
00:06:43,733 --> 00:06:45,866
but to make a precision assembler

137
00:06:45,866 --> 00:06:48,600
we need some dope naquadah wafers

138
00:06:49,300 --> 00:06:51,800
the convenience store doesn't keep them

139
00:06:51,800 --> 00:06:55,866
so we have to go with the poors man way of making naquadah

140
00:06:56,800 --> 00:06:59,600
and with those small amounts made in an ugly way

141
00:06:59,600 --> 00:07:02,300
we have just enough for our precision assembler

142
00:07:03,033 --> 00:07:03,533
however

143
00:07:03,533 --> 00:07:06,133
that was just the controller block

144
00:07:06,333 --> 00:07:08,866
we also need a stack of the casings

145
00:07:09,800 --> 00:07:11,833
and here we run into an issue

146
00:07:11,833 --> 00:07:13,666
we need an LuV assembler

147
00:07:14,800 --> 00:07:17,100
so I guess we should go back on track

148
00:07:17,100 --> 00:07:20,700
and start working on the assembly line for the Luv tier

149
00:07:21,000 --> 00:07:23,833
but I think this deserves its own episode

150
00:07:24,066 --> 00:07:25,033
bye bye

151
00:00:00,300 --> 00:00:01,433
欢迎回来！

152
00:00:01,600 --> 00:00:04,666
今天我们要做一些火箭燃料

153
00:00:04,800 --> 00:00:07,700
第一步是用重铬酸钾粉

154
00:00:08,033 --> 00:00:10,433
来制造邻苯二甲酸

155
00:00:11,033 --> 00:00:13,000
制作出重铬酸钾的方法多多

156
00:00:13,000 --> 00:00:16,800
而最有效率的需要 ZPM 化学反应釜

157
00:00:17,133 --> 00:00:20,133
由于 LuV 级别我们都未曾涉足

158
00:00:20,200 --> 00:00:23,633
我们将通过八仓升压来达到 ZPM 级

159
00:00:24,200 --> 00:00:27,600
即使我们将电池全部充满

160
00:00:27,600 --> 00:00:30,000
机器还是无法正常工作

161
00:00:30,300 --> 00:00:30,566
因此

162
00:00:30,566 --> 00:00:32,966
我们再用两个小化反进行额外反应

163
00:00:32,966 --> 00:00:35,700
用来降低大化反配方要求

164
00:00:35,933 --> 00:00:38,400
现在我们便得到了

165
00:00:38,400 --> 00:00:40,100
用于制作邻苯二甲酸的重铬酸钾

166
00:00:40,633 --> 00:00:42,833
邻苯二甲酸大有其用

167
00:00:42,833 --> 00:00:44,866
第一个用处

168
00:00:44,866 --> 00:00:47,000
便是制作间苯二甲酸二苯酯

169
00:00:47,933 --> 00:00:49,933
而这是制作聚苯并咪唑所需的

170
00:00:49,933 --> 00:00:52,400
两种必备材料之一

171
00:00:52,466 --> 00:00:54,600
它简称为 PBI

172
00:00:55,666 --> 00:00:58,800
另一种材料是 3,3-二氨基联苯胺

173
00:01:00,533 --> 00:01:05,333
通过 3,3-二氯联苯胺便可轻松获取

174
00:01:06,033 --> 00:01:08,900
而我们使用 2-硝基氯苯制造它

175
00:01:09,600 --> 00:01:11,266
现在我们有了 PBI

176
00:01:11,266 --> 00:01:13,800
一套更加优秀的隔热装置便呼之欲出

177
00:01:13,800 --> 00:01:17,300
这将帮助我们使用新火箭进行太空探索时

178
00:01:17,300 --> 00:01:19,333
保护我们安然无恙

179
00:01:19,733 --> 00:01:22,300
但我们似乎好像遗漏了什么事情

180
00:01:22,700 --> 00:01:26,200
我们不是为了 PBI 来制造邻苯二甲酸

181
00:01:26,333 --> 00:01:27,833
而是为了火箭燃料

182
00:01:27,933 --> 00:01:30,633
所以让我们回去进行脱水

183
00:01:30,633 --> 00:01:33,066
来获得点邻苯二甲酸酐粉

184
00:01:33,500 --> 00:01:35,600
我们把它带到化工厂

185
00:01:35,600 --> 00:01:37,600
让它和乙苯发生反应

186
00:01:37,600 --> 00:01:40,233
于是便获得了 2-乙基蔥醌

187
00:01:40,666 --> 00:01:42,333
此流体将在反应中完全循环

188
00:01:42,333 --> 00:01:44,733
我们将液体导入一个自动化过程

189
00:01:44,733 --> 00:01:46,266
用于进一步处理

190
00:01:46,700 --> 00:01:50,900
这个化工厂将自给自足许多产品

191
00:01:50,900 --> 00:01:53,133
但是让我们聚焦于其中一种

192
00:01:53,933 --> 00:01:54,400
第一步

193
00:01:54,400 --> 00:01:59,100
我们将 2-乙基蒽菎变成 2-乙基蒽氢菎

194
00:01:59,500 --> 00:02:02,533
它将用于制作过氧化氢

195
00:02:02,700 --> 00:02:06,333
此过程也会返还一些 2-乙基蒽菎

196
00:02:06,666 --> 00:02:10,200
最后加入一些其他东西来制造肼

197
00:02:11,033 --> 00:02:13,466
这便是所有的原料输入仓

198
00:02:13,500 --> 00:02:17,100
唯一要做的便是开机

199
00:02:18,666 --> 00:02:21,333
一旦肼开始生产

200
00:02:21,333 --> 00:02:24,000
我们可以从 ME 终端中直接拿取

201
00:02:25,100 --> 00:02:28,933
我们手动加入一些甲醇得到密集肼火箭燃料

202
00:02:28,933 --> 00:02:32,666
而这是能在 T3 火箭中使用的一种燃料

203
00:02:34,200 --> 00:02:36,433
一旦新火箭的燃料完成填充

204
00:02:36,433 --> 00:02:39,500
新的行星卫星便不再遥远

205
00:02:40,466 --> 00:02:43,133
我们主要目的地是谷神星

206
00:02:43,133 --> 00:02:46,000
在那里可以找到铂矿脉

207
00:02:46,333 --> 00:02:48,333
在等待矿机完成工作的同时

208
00:02:48,333 --> 00:02:52,233
我们着手于 IV 任务的最后一条化学链

209
00:02:52,233 --> 00:02:53,266
独居石处理

210
00:02:53,900 --> 00:02:56,600
这条化学生产线需要一些粉碎矿

211
00:02:56,600 --> 00:02:59,533
而我们已用其他方法完成处理

212
00:02:59,800 --> 00:03:01,866
为了确保它们进入这条产线

213
00:03:01,900 --> 00:03:05,266
我们将抽屉上的存储总线调成最优先

214
00:03:06,200 --> 00:03:06,933
还有这里

215
00:03:06,933 --> 00:03:10,500
不同于平常的矿处机器

216
00:03:10,500 --> 00:03:14,233
我们将用煮解池来进行处理

217
00:03:15,033 --> 00:03:17,933
输出物将进入溶解罐

218
00:03:18,200 --> 00:03:23,200
而这台机器要求输入流体具有特殊比例

219
00:03:23,800 --> 00:03:27,333
所以要精准且缓慢地输入它们

220
00:03:27,333 --> 00:03:30,933
而流体探测覆盖板能胜任这份工作

221
00:03:31,466 --> 00:03:34,666
一旦输入仓有了 9 kL 液体

222
00:03:34,666 --> 00:03:37,666
它便停止抽取

223
00:03:37,933 --> 00:03:40,333
我们对另一个输入仓故技重施

224
00:03:40,933 --> 00:03:44,300
一旦液体输入调整完毕

225
00:03:44,300 --> 00:03:48,300
第二个步骤便可以顺利进行

226
00:03:48,866 --> 00:03:52,233
输出物必须经过筛选才能获得大量产物

227
00:03:52,233 --> 00:03:56,100
而我们最关心的便是硫酸独居石粉

228
00:03:56,833 --> 00:03:59,000
将其用硝酸洗个澡

229
00:03:59,500 --> 00:04:00,866
再筛选一次

230
00:04:01,433 --> 00:04:04,100
高炉中快速烘烤

231
00:04:04,666 --> 00:04:06,700
再与硝酸反应一次

232
00:04:07,400 --> 00:04:09,500
然后加上其他化学反应物

233
00:04:10,266 --> 00:04:13,866
又又筛选一次

234
00:04:14,266 --> 00:04:16,900
随后将其冷冻

235
00:04:17,633 --> 00:04:22,266
使用磁通量效应监视器中电磁离析模式

236
00:04:22,300 --> 00:04:25,600
来剔除那些非铁磁性的成分

237
00:04:25,733 --> 00:04:28,300
我们复用之前的高炉提取出

238
00:04:28,300 --> 00:04:32,533
异质卤化独居石稀土混合物粉

239
00:04:32,666 --> 00:04:36,266
我们把它与其他物品搅拌至饱和

240
00:04:36,466 --> 00:04:39,533
再通入离心机分开

241
00:04:39,800 --> 00:04:43,000
再筛出少量钐粉

242
00:04:43,133 --> 00:04:46,466
而这是下一电压中马达的必需品

243
00:04:46,633 --> 00:04:49,033
我们做完了镧系处理的主线

244
00:04:49,033 --> 00:04:52,333
但还有些支线没做

245
00:04:52,333 --> 00:04:54,233
接着干

246
00:04:54,600 --> 00:04:58,000
我们打算重复利用大部分机器

247
00:04:58,433 --> 00:05:01,266
既然在做奇怪的矿物处理了

248
00:05:01,266 --> 00:05:04,100
我们不妨继续做氟碳铈矿处理

249
00:05:04,233 --> 00:05:05,733
这条产线更像流水线

250
00:05:05,733 --> 00:05:07,933
而它的主要输出是狄粉

251
00:05:08,100 --> 00:05:09,333
我们将又一次

252
00:05:09,333 --> 00:05:12,466
尽可能地多重复利用机器

253
00:05:12,866 --> 00:05:16,300
现在我们回谷神星取回铂矿

254
00:05:16,300 --> 00:05:17,633
一回到家

255
00:05:17,633 --> 00:05:20,033
我们便发现了一个惊喜

256
00:05:20,233 --> 00:05:22,033
我们还收集到了一些硅岩矿

257
00:05:22,033 --> 00:05:26,066
这将开启一条更有趣的化学产线

258
00:05:26,833 --> 00:05:30,066
不像之前存在于现实的产线

259
00:05:30,066 --> 00:05:34,433
这条产线将更多基于奇思妙想

260
00:05:34,833 --> 00:05:38,000
首先准备一些碎冰

261
00:05:38,700 --> 00:05:40,900
再加入些许锑粉

262
00:05:40,933 --> 00:05:42,600
但由于添加太多化学物

263
00:05:42,600 --> 00:05:45,700
现在它看起来像以前的化学物质之一

264
00:05:46,300 --> 00:05:47,666
所以我们对其进行蒸馏

265
00:05:47,666 --> 00:05:51,100
看看能浓缩到什么地步

266
00:05:51,733 --> 00:05:54,100
但我们希望它酸一点

267
00:05:54,100 --> 00:05:56,100
所以我们让它显酸性

268
00:05:56,800 --> 00:05:57,433
而现在

269
00:05:57,433 --> 00:06:00,733
是添加主要成分的最佳时机

270
00:06:00,733 --> 00:06:01,800
氧化硅岩混合物粉

271
00:06:02,666 --> 00:06:03,700
通过高炉烧制后

272
00:06:03,700 --> 00:06:07,533
我们使用离心机来分离出那些锑粉

273
00:06:08,600 --> 00:06:11,000
但这些材料纯度仍然很低

274
00:06:11,000 --> 00:06:15,433
所以我们得加点调味料，如P-507

275
00:06:16,200 --> 00:06:18,033
如你所见

276
00:06:18,033 --> 00:06:20,666
我们已经获得了高纯度的硅岩粉了

277
00:06:20,666 --> 00:06:24,000
正因为我们使用的P-507质量上乘

278
00:06:24,100 --> 00:06:26,833
它是通过人工种植有机坚果

279
00:06:26,833 --> 00:06:28,600
提取其油分制成的

280
00:06:29,266 --> 00:06:32,833
最后一步将其通入中子活化器

281
00:06:32,833 --> 00:06:34,900
让其在我们齿颊留香

282
00:06:35,866 --> 00:06:36,400
然而

283
00:06:36,400 --> 00:06:40,200
我们缺少完成这步骤所需的烹饪工具

284
00:06:40,200 --> 00:06:40,966
想要获取一个的话

285
00:06:40,966 --> 00:06:43,033
我们需要一个精密组装机

286
00:06:43,733 --> 00:06:45,866
但制作它

287
00:06:45,866 --> 00:06:48,600
我们需要一些硅岩掺杂的晶圆

288
00:06:49,300 --> 00:06:51,800
因为便利店不提供售卖服务

289
00:06:51,800 --> 00:06:55,866
所以我们得先用土法制硅岩

290
00:06:56,800 --> 00:06:59,600
有了这些不入流方法获得的硅岩

291
00:06:59,600 --> 00:07:02,300
我们将能制作出第一台精密组装机

292
00:07:03,033 --> 00:07:03,533
然而

293
00:07:03,533 --> 00:07:06,133
那只是主方块

294
00:07:06,333 --> 00:07:08,866
我们还需要一堆电子机械外壳

295
00:07:09,800 --> 00:07:11,833
而同时一个难题接踵而至

296
00:07:11,833 --> 00:07:13,666
我们需要一台 LuV 级组装机

297
00:07:14,800 --> 00:07:17,100
所以我想我们应该回到主线

298
00:07:17,100 --> 00:07:20,700
开始做通向 LuV 的装配线

299
00:07:21,000 --> 00:07:23,833
但我觉得这值得单独出一集

300
00:07:24,066 --> 00:07:25,033
所以再见~

301
00:00:20,200 --> 00:00:23,633
（最新版已禁止此方法）

302
00:02:52,233 --> 00:02:53,266
（臭名昭著的镧系处理）

303
00:04:22,300 --> 00:04:25,600
（除了具有铁磁性的铁钴镍以外，其他元素构成的化合物对磁场的反应微弱）

304
00:04:43,133 --> 00:04:46,466
LuV

